org.gearvrf

Class GVRAndroidResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gearvrf.GVRAndroidResource

  • public class GVRAndroidResource
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to minimize overload fan-out. APIs that load resources can take a GVRAndroidResource instead of having overloads for assets files, res/drawable and res/raw files, and plain old files. See the discussion of asset-relative filenames vs. R.raw resource ids in the package description.
    Since:
    1.6.1

      • getStream

        public final java.io.InputStream getStream()

        Returns:
        An open InputStream.

      • closeStream

        public final void closeStream()
        Close the open stream. It's OK to call code that closes the stream for you - the only point of this API is to update the debug state (visible via toString()) to CLOSED.

      • mark

        public void mark()
        Save the stream position, for later use with reset(). All GVRAndroidResource streams support mark() and reset(). Calling mark() right after construction will allow you to read the header then rewind the stream if you can't handle the file format.
        Since:
        1.6.7

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Restore the stream position, to the point set by a previous mark(). Please note that calling reset() generally 'consumes' the mark() - do not call 
         mark();
